\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{A}$
\end_inset

 and the columns of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{B}\mathbf{P}$
\end_inset

 are linearly independent, as each zero row of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{B}\mathbf{P}$
\end_inset

 is occupied by a 
\begin_inset Formula $-1$
\end_inset

 from a column of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{A}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

